# Project: CreativePhotoEditor

A free, browser-first, simplified Photoshop alternative (layers, move/resize,
blend, export). Browser is the MVP; Windows/mac/mobile come later by wrapping the
same browser core. Full design docs live in `CreativePhotoEditor-cursor-package/`
(PROJECT_BRAIN, ARCHITECTURE, ROADMAP, TAXONOMY) — read those before large work.

## Stack overrides
- Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript strict.
- Rendering: PixiJS (WebGL) — imported ONLY inside `core/render`.
- UI state: Zustand (`state/`) mirrors the LayerGraph; the LayerGraph is the source of truth.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS. File I/O: JSZip for the `.cpe` container.
- Deploy: Vercel (main → Production, dev → Preview). Repo: github.com/nathanokh1/CreativePhotoEditor.

## Conventions
- Every LayerGraph mutation goes through a Command (`core/commands`) — never mutate
  the graph directly from a React handler. Undo/redo is not optional.
- Use TAXONOMY.md terms exactly (Document, Layer, Command, Export vs Save, etc.).
- Keep the `core/` layer framework-agnostic (no React/Next imports) so it survives
  a future Tauri/mobile wrap.
- KISS. If a feature isn't in the current ROADMAP phase, it's out of scope.

## Notes
- Current phase: Phase 1 (MVP core loop) — import → layer → move/scale → export → save/load .cpe.
- Forge tooling lives in `/forge` (gitignored; its own repo at github.com/nathanokh1/Forge).
